== A Test Equation

The OLS estimator minimises the residual sum of squares. Given a linear model $bold(y) = bold(X) bold(beta) + bold(epsilon)$, the solution is

$ bold(hat(beta)) = (bold(X)^top bold(X))^(-1) bold(X)^top bold(y). $ <eq:ols>

